013package org.apache.juneau.annotation;
014
015import static java.lang.annotation.ElementType.*;
016import static java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy.*;
017
018import java.lang.annotation.*;
019
020/**
021 * Annotation that can be used on method parameters to identify their name.
022 *
023 * <p>
024 * Can be used in the following locations:
025 * <ul>
026 *    <li>On constructor and method arguments when the parameter names are not in the compiled bytecode.
027 * </ul>
028 *
029 * <h5 class='figure'>Examples:</h5>
030 * <p class='bjava'>
031 *    <jc>// Identifying bean property names.
032 *    // The field name can be anything.</jc>
033 *    <jk>public class</jk> MyBean {
034 *
035 *       <jk>public</jk> MyBean(<ja>@Name</ja>(<js>"bar"</js>) <jk>int</jk> <jv>foo</jv>) {}
036 *    }
037 * </p>
038 *
039 * <ul class='seealso'>
040
041 * </ul>
042 */
043@Documented
044@Target({PARAMETER})
045@Retention(RUNTIME)
046@Inherited
047public @interface Name {
048
049   /**
050    * The bean property or parameter name.
051    *
052    * @return The annotation value.
053    */
054   String value();
055}
